Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel!).

Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, then season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat, then spread out and roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

Pop the @lamb strips{200} in a #bowl{} with the @rogan josh curry paste{50} and a spoonful of @low fat natural yoghurt{150}. Mix well and set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Halve the @green pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pop the pepper onto a #roasting tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roast until soft and slightly charred, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Halve, peel and finely slice the @red onion{1}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Pull the @mint{1}(leaves only, roughly chopped) leaves off their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Mix the remaining yogurt with half the mint, season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and stir to combine.

> Tip: if you have any washing up do this now.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} over high heat. Add the tomatoes and onion, cook until soft and jammy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add a @?sugar{pinch} if you have any. Once the onion and tomatoes have softened, add the lamb and cook until golden all over, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Pop the @plain naans{2} on a #baking tray{} in the oven for ~{3-4%minutes} to warm through.

Divide the naans between plates then top with the lamb mixture. Top this with the roasted pepper, followed by a drizzle of the minty yogurt sauce and a sprinkle of the remaining mint. Serve with wedges alongside. Enjoy!